      • getContents

        public List<SBOLRootObject> getContents()
        Returns the top-level objects contained in this document. Top level objects may contain other SBOL objects. For example, a DnaComponent may contain a DnaSequence and multiple SequenceAnnotations which will not be included in the results of this function. To get all the objects contained in a document you can use the SBOLObjectCollector function.
        Specified by:
        getContents in interface SBOLDocument

      • addContent
